commit_message:
Merge pull request #5 from oskar-taubert/master

More convenient manipulation of alignments between preprocessing and computation of MFDCA
dca class can now take msa as either a filename or a biopython alignment object
decoupled fasta file reading from transforming alignment from letter to integer representation
added consistency test for more flexible interface
updated version number for next release

Merge pull request #1 from MehariBZ/master

Merge pull request #1 from KIT-MBS/master
removed whole pydca import from example notebook
upgraded biopython to version 1.74 to avoid deprecation warning of the fasta reader
fixed bug that assigns lambda_h to lambda_J

Merge pull request #1 from KIT-MBS/master

synchronizing pydca fork
downgraded matplotlib for compatibility with Python 3.5
added exception when the number of requested DCA contacts exceeds PDB contacts
updated RNA test input MSA file path
site mapping is forwareded to methods
added seqbackmapper as named arg, modified MeanFieldDCA constructor
removed site-pair mapping from output writer
adder url for Ipython Notebook rendering option
changed zero initializations to float type
added method to obtain DCA ranked pairs from a list
read only non-redundant sequences from FASTA file
corrected shape of arrays for shifting couplings
added num_thread and verbose params to command line
adjusted the ordering of logging message
plmdca c++ backend souce first commit
changed seq. weight computation to parallel loop
updated residue mappings to include all letters
separated PlmDCA class from plmdca_main module
corrected spelling from standared to standard
added PDB downloading method when a PDB id is supplied insted of a local PDB file
shared object location through python module added
added command line interface for plmDCA
changed couplings output file header metadata
added a function to write params
removed imported but unused module fasta_reader
modified how alignment attribute is read, added logging message message
added function to write trimmed MSA
changed logging message for non-standared residues
changed logging level WARN to WARNING
